The paper focuses on video captioning, which involves analyzing visual features and generating natural language sentences. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories, including computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with multimodal data (visual and semantic), which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel architecture that leverages attention mechanisms, which is a popular area of research in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
